-- German Car Sales to Grow 41% in U.S. by 2015, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-01-09T09:01:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/german-car-sales-to-grow-41-in-u-s-by-2015-handelsblatt-says.html
German carmakers will sell 41 percent
more vehicles in the U.S. by 2015,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing
a report by the University of Duisburg-Essen’s  Center for
Automotive Research .  German manufacturers’ production capacity will grow to 1.59
million units from 965,000 during the period, Handelsblatt said,
citing the report. The companies’ market share, which was 7.6
percent in 2010, will climb to 9.9 percent, Handelsblatt said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at   cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 